Dorsal fin with scattered dark pigments bordering rays along their length. Anal fin with scattered dark pigments bordering fin rays, more concentrated along its proximal and distal length, resulting in a somewhat clearer medial area in few individuals. Adipose fin with scattered dark chromatophores along its area, except for its distal one third, which is hyaline. Paired fins hyaline with scattered dark pigments, more concentrated on intermembranes of unbranched ray. Midregion of both caudal-fin lobes with a field of dark chromatophores. Tips and base of both lobes of caudal fin hyaline (fig. 
1
).
